Xinhua News Review: Turn outstanding returning migrant workers into a new force for rural revitalization-Xinhuanet
Talents are the key to rural revitalization.
Where to find talents?
Outstanding returning migrant workers are an indispensable force.
Xinhua News Agency Issued by Shang Hai Chunzuo
Xinhua News Agency, Chengdu, July 26th. Topic: Turn outstanding returning migrant workers into a new force for rural revitalization
Zhang Xiong, 34, lives in Guoyuan Village, Meishan City, Sichuan. In 2010, he quit his job in Beijing with a monthly salary of tens of thousands and returned to his hometown to start a business.
After several years of hard work, the annual income of his grape-growing family farm now exceeds one million yuan. He has become a well-known leader in getting rich. He has also been selected to join the village's "two committees" team.
In recent years, inspired by a series of policies to support agriculture and benefit agriculture, such as national poverty alleviation and rural revitalization, more and more outstanding migrant workers like Zhang Xiong have chosen to return to their hometowns to start their own businesses, which has activated a pool of spring water in the countryside.
Sichuan, a province with a large population in western my country and a large labor exporting province, has implemented the "Excellent Migrant Workers Recruitment Training Project" according to the situation. In 2019 alone, more than 8,000 village party branch secretaries were generated from the outstanding migrant workers to cultivate village reserve forces. There are 61,000 members and more than 20,000 party members will be recruited to provide a strong guarantee for winning the battle against poverty and implementing the strategy of rural revitalization.
Whether or not a well-off society is well-off, the key depends on the fellow villagers.
Since the reform and opening up, a large number of young and middle-aged laborers in rural my country have gone out to work to increase their income, and some have established their own enterprises through hard work.
However, objectively it has also led to the emergence of "hollowing" to varying degrees in rural areas, especially the weakening of rural grassroots organizations. The village party branch secretaries and party members all show the characteristics of "one old and one low", that is, aging, low education, and the village party The team leader is not strong, and the problem of non-compliance is prominent.
If rural talents and other factors have been flowing unidirectionally to the cities, and the rural areas have been in a state of "blood loss" and "anemia" for a long time, revitalization is empty talk.
Attracting back those migrant workers who are capable, conscious, and aspiring to serve their hometowns, guide them to return to their hometowns to start businesses and become wealthy leaders, and select the best to train them into party members and rural cadres, and enrich the grassroots cadre team. This is to solve the problem of rural party members. A permanent solution that is not in contact with the grassroots party organizations.
Excellent migrant workers can be attracted back, but they must be retained and done well.
In recent years, Sichuan has begun to pay close attention to the party building of migrant workers. On the basis of strict selection criteria, it has established systems and mechanisms for outstanding migrant workers’ directional referral, service guarantee, training and promotion, selection and use, etc., so that they can improve their abilities and work. There is a guarantee of security, a hope in life, a real root in the countryside, and a sense of accomplishment in starting a business.
This year is the final year of the decisive battle against poverty. To make the connection between poverty alleviation and rural revitalization, talents are the key factor.
Party committees and governments at all levels should attach great importance to the group of outstanding returning rural migrant workers, and through comprehensive measures, build them into a team and a new force that can be retained, fight, and cannot be taken away, so as to provide the rural areas with poverty alleviation and prosperity and development and revitalization. Strong organizational guarantee and talent support.
