According to the Russian newspaper Izvestia a few days ago, Wuzhika-52M is called "Super Alligator". Its development contract was signed by the Russian military and military units in April last year. Currently, the first batch of two of the upgraded version of Wuzhi is currently in Russia. The Far East Helicopter Manufacturing Plant of Progressive Aerospace Corporation has undergone transformation and refurbishment, and its national-level testing and improvement work will be completed before October 2022.
According to Russian experts who understand the above-mentioned upgrade work, the "predecessor" of the "Super Alligator"-Wuzhika-52 was officially installed in November 2011. This model has exposed some weaknesses during use. It is to "make up for shortcomings."
According to the report, compared with the Ka-52, the Ka-52M will partially adopt new protective materials that will not increase the weight. Its pilot cockpit will be reinforced and equipped with new equipment to resist missile attacks, thereby increasing the probability of survival on the battlefield; the assembly power is greater. In order to power more complex airborne electronic equipment; the photoelectric system has been upgraded to detect and identify targets on the battlefield that are farther apart; the new light multi-purpose missile, which is equipped with main attack armored combat vehicles and reinforced concrete fortifications, has a range Up to 20 kilometers, the range of similar missiles used by Russia’s active military helicopters is approximately doubled; its defensive weapons and communication equipment will be used as much as possible with the Mi-28NM armed helicopters that can attack air targets, making related maintenance simple and economical. .
In addition, Ka-52M will have more advanced electronic guidance systems, weapon targeting systems and navigation equipment.
Russian experts also said that it is worth noting that Ka-52M will be equipped with communication equipment to communicate with drones, so as to obtain real-time information transmitted by nearby drones in the air. image.
According to the plan, the pilots of the Ka-52M can directly control the drones that cooperate with them, thereby improving the pilot's grasp of the battlefield situation and the guidance of long-range missiles.
According to Russian media reports, Russian Deputy Defense Minister Krivoruchko stated in December last year that the Russian Defense Ministry plans to purchase more than 110 Wuzhika-52Ms by 2027.
