"Screw on the Jiangnan" to pursue the poetic "Yellow River Dream"-Chinanews.com
(Chinese Poverty Reduction Story) "Screw on the South of the Yangtze River" Pursuing the Poetic "Yellow River Dream"
China News Service, Yinchuan, July 26 (Yang Di) "The Nine-curved Yellow River has tens of thousands of li sands, and the waves and wind rush from the end of the world."
The Yellow River, which aroused countless literati's lofty passions, gave birth to the beautiful and fertile Ningxia Plain. Today, Ningxia, which has the reputation of "Stopping Jiangnan", is adhering to the concept of "ecology first, green development" and pursuing the poetic "Yellow River Dream".
The beautiful "Bibo Dream" of the river
"The Yellow River in the world enriches Ningxia", the Yellow River flows 397 kilometers through Ningxia and is the "mother river" for nurturing a party.
However, with the rapid advancement of industrialization and urbanization, the development, utilization, management and protection of rivers and lakes have become unbalanced, and chaos such as excessive sewage discharge, lake reclamation, and infringement of waters have emerged, resulting in black and odorous water, excessive water quality, dirty environment, and ecological degradation.
Now, Ningxia is promoting the restoration of diverse water ecology and working hard to make the Yellow River beautiful and clear.
Water control must start from the source.
In Yinchuan, Ningxia, the local government adopted the method of "standard improvement + pollution control + strict management". All sewage in the industrial parks were treated in a centralized manner. The urban sewage treatment plants all achieved Class A discharge standards. The black and odorous water bodies in urban built-up areas were basically eliminated, and the application was successfully declared The third batch of China's black and smelly water demonstration cities.
In addition, Ningxia fully implemented the river and lake chief system in 2017, and now it has achieved full coverage of the five-level river and lake chief responsibility system in districts, counties and villages, and long patrols of rivers and lakes have become the norm.
64-year-old Gu Jincheng lives in a village by the Yellow River. He has witnessed the changes in the Yellow River: “The previous water smelled like a smell, but after the rectification, the smell disappeared.”
Gu Jincheng said that the ecological environment is better and his life is more comfortable. Now he often walks by the Yellow River with his family and feels the blue water and blue sky.
Sha Ouxiang's "Wetland Dream"
Birds, green trees, plank roads, clear water... The beauty of Fan Zhongyan's "Sand Gulls Xiangji" has become a reality in the Yellow River Wetland Park in Yinchuan, Ningxia.
The Yellow River flows through Ningxia, forming river wetlands, lake wetlands, marsh wetlands and other wetlands along the way, which play an important role in promoting the rational use of water resources and the water ecological balance. It has also become an important international bird migration channel.
Since 2009, relevant departments in Ningxia have invested a total of 3.45 billion yuan in wetland protection projects. At present, Yinchuan wetland covers an area of 19,200 hectares, with a wetland protection rate of 78.5%. There are nearly 200 natural lakes and marsh wetlands. There are 5 national wetland parks, 1 national urban wetland park, 6 autonomous region-level wetland parks, and 8 municipal-level parks.
Lu Jinhu, deputy director of the Yinchuan Wetland Conservation Center, told reporters that wetland protection has increased biodiversity, which is particularly evident in birds. “The relict gull is an endangered bird, and there are only more than 20,000 in the world. Among them, the Yinchuan Wetland There are more than 2,000 inhabitants."
At the same time, Ningxia has delineated a 500-meter red line for the wetland protection areas on both sides of the Yinchuan section of the Yellow River in accordance with the law, stipulating that no unit or individual may conduct development, construction and business activities within the protected area except for public welfare projects.
Zhao Shaoyong, deputy director of Yinchuan Water Conservancy Service Center, introduced that through pollution source treatment, comprehensive improvement of river and lake ecology, and terminal wetland construction, 100% of the water quality of Ningxia’s nine main drainage ditches into the Yellow River has reached Class IV standards. “Now the water is clear. The fish swam and the flowers bloomed."
The "Drinking Dream" of Inclusive People's Livelihood
Yinchuan City in Ningxia used to have the title of "embarrassing": the only city along the Yellow River that "guarded the water shortage of the Yellow River".
Since 2010, Yinchuan City has been facing persistent water shortages during the peak summer period. The pain of water shortage in the past ten years has become a painful summer experience for many high-floor residents. Under the current situation that a large area of groundwater over-exploitation funnel area has formed under the limit of mining and urban underground, water shortage has become a problem that plagues Yinchuan City.
Thanks to the improvement of the water quality of the Yellow River, drinking purified Yellow River water has become a good way to solve the drinking water problems of local residents.
According to Ding Ming, deputy director of Yinchuan Water Affairs Bureau, in order to improve the water demand of urban and rural residents in Yinchuan, Ningxia started the water supply project of the West Line of Yinchuan Metropolitan Area at an appropriate time to replace the original underground water source with high-quality Yellow River water.
"On December 29, 2019, the water supply project officially provided water to the three districts of Yinchuan City. In 2020, residents of Minning Town and Helan County will also drink water from the Yellow River."
Ding Ming said that the Yinchuan Water Conservancy Department will make overall plans to consider the integration of rural drinking water and urban water supply in the region. “In the next step, we will integrate all the scattered water supply points in rural areas and connect them to the west line water supply project. It is expected that the Yinchuan area will be basically achieved by the end of this year. Integrated urban and rural water supply."
