Xinhua News Agency, Shenzhen, July 26 (Reporters Mao Siqian and Bai Yu) Encourage residents to do physical examinations frequently to detect problems early; prohibit the sale of alcoholic beverages to minors; establish a health review system for online games; employers must be equipped with full-time and part-time health management personnel ...... The "Shenzhen Special Economic Zone Health Regulations (Draft for Comment)" was officially released a few days ago, and Shenzhen residents will have their own "health law."
In order to encourage residents to do physical examinations frequently and find problems as early as possible, the above-mentioned consultation draft proposes that the health department should develop a basic catalog of health examination items based on factors such as age and occupation.
The cost of a health check-up within the scope of the basic list of health check-up items shall be paid by the social medical insurance coordinating fund at the standard of once per person per year.
The draft for comments clearly stated that employers should rationally allocate human resources, arrange staff working hours, and implement a rotation system for employees with heavy mental and physical workloads to avoid excessive loss of human functions or physical and mental health damage to employees’ health, and strict implementation Paid leave system for employees.
In addition, the employer must be equipped with full-time and part-time health management personnel, and regularly organize and carry out employee health examinations.
Regarding the physical and mental health of minors, the draft for comments proposes that the sale of alcoholic beverages to minors is prohibited, and at the same time the sales location of alcoholic beverages is restricted. For violations of the regulations, the market supervision and management department will order corrections and impose a penalty of 30,000 yuan. fine.
In addition to "prohibition", minors must also "exercise more."
According to the requirements of the draft, the school should arrange more than one hour of student sports activities every day.
For online games, the public security, culture, broadcasting, television, tourism, sports, network supervision, health and health departments should improve the health supervision system of Internet service business premises, establish a health review system for online games, and create a good communication space and culture for promoting the healthy growth of young people.
In addition, the draft also proposes that influenza patients must wear masks when entering and leaving public places, and medical and health institutions will fine 20,000 yuan for leaking patients' privacy without consent.
It is worth noting that, in addition to the physical and mental health of residents, the draft also requires that various departments in Shenzhen are formulating plans involving urban spatial planning and construction, industrial park planning and construction, resource development and utilization, ecological environment protection, and biomedical industry development. , Before the regulatory documents and approval of major construction projects and implementation of major public service projects, the impact of public policy implementation on the health of the population should be assessed.
Those that have not been assessed or will have a serious adverse impact on urban public health or the health of residents shall not be formulated, promulgated or approved for implementation.
