In recent years, as people’s lifestyles have changed and the pace of life has accelerated, China has become the world’s largest country with hypertension, and aortic diseases have also increased. Nowadays, with the development of surgical techniques and industrial materials, the treatment of aortic diseases Continue to develop in the direction of minimally invasive, fast and efficient.
Doctors can puncture the thigh and place a stent in the aorta to properly "divert" the blood flow to avoid the impact on aneurysm or ruptured dissection and achieve a good therapeutic effect. Some operations even require local anesthesia.
This academic seminar invited more than ten domestic experts to discuss the new progress in the treatment of aortic disease, and carried out cutting-edge technical training and difficult case discussions in the form of a conference salon.
The reporter learned at the meeting that with the development of surgical technology and industrial materials, the current treatment of aortic diseases continues to develop in a minimally invasive, rapid and efficient direction.
