Employment and prices are generally stable, demonstrating the "temperature" of the economy
Lin Huocan, reporter of Economic Daily and China Economic Net
In the first half of this year, facing the impact of the new crown pneumonia epidemic, my country has coordinated efforts to promote epidemic prevention and control and economic and social development. The epidemic prevention and control situation has continued to improve, the economy has been recovering steadily, and the performance of employment and prices that are closely related to people's livelihood are generally stable. , China's economy has handed over a report card of economic performance with warmth.
In the first two months of this year, the surveyed unemployment rate increased.
Especially in February, many enterprises' production and operation activities were basically in a state of suspension of work and production, and enterprises' labor demand decreased, recruitment was delayed or cancelled, and the surveyed unemployment rate in cities and towns increased.
With the gradual improvement of the epidemic prevention and control situation, the production and life order of the whole society has been continuously restored.
The Party Central Committee adheres to the general tone of seeking progress while maintaining stability, further intensifies macro-policy hedging, comprehensively strengthens the employment priority policy, and actively promotes assistance to enterprises to stabilize jobs and expand employment.
my country has stepped up policy hedging to stabilize jobs, hit the "reduction, exemption, delay, return and compensation" policy combination, phased reduction and exemption of three social insurance unit payment parts, allowing deferred payment of social insurance premiums, and expanding the unemployment insurance for small and medium-sized enterprises to reimburse the stable jobs and pay for workers. For the benefit of the training policy, enterprises will be given subsidies for absorbing the employment of key groups, subsidies for internships, etc.
With the implementation of various employment stabilization policies, the demand for employment by enterprises has steadily picked up, the employment situation has gradually improved, and the surveyed unemployment rate in urban areas has gradually decreased. In June, the surveyed unemployment rate was 5.7%.
Zhang Yi, director of the Population and Employment Statistics Department of the National Bureau of Statistics, said that in the second quarter, various employment policies continued to be effective. The labor force who withdrew due to the impact of the epidemic in the early stage returned one after another. The urban labor participation rate in June increased by about 10 percentage points compared with February. The level was close to the same period last year.
Data show that the total urban employment in June increased by more than 19% compared with February, and most industries reached the pre-epidemic level; the average weekly working hours of corporate employees reached 46.8 hours, an increase of 6.6 hours from February and slightly higher than January by 0.1 hours.
Prices are also related to millions of households.
In January this year, the CPI rose by 5.4% year-on-year, setting a new high for many years.
Entering February, although the year-on-year increase of CPI fell slightly, it was still in the “5 range”.
The year-on-year growth rate of CPI is at a high level, due to factors driving consumer demand before the Spring Festival, as well as factors such as the wrong month of the Spring Festival and a low year-on-year base.
However, the impact of the new crown pneumonia epidemic on prices is particularly obvious.
Affected by the prevention and control of the epidemic, in January and February, there were delays in logistics, untimely supply of materials, and increased transportation costs of materials in various parts of the country. In addition, some citizens were hoarding and rushing to buy, and the prices of some daily necessities increased significantly.
In response to the disturbances caused by the epidemic prevention and control to the price situation, relevant departments included important living materials into the scope of emergency transportation guarantee to ensure smooth transportation of materials.
Thanks to a series of policy measures, the market supply of vegetables and fruits has been strongly guaranteed.
In response to the rapid increase in pork prices at the beginning of this year, after the central government promulgated the policy of ensuring supply and stabilizing prices, various regions and departments quickly implemented them. The supply of pork reserves has improved significantly, the production capacity of live pigs has been restored in an orderly manner, and the order of production and sales has gradually become normal.
Since March, pork prices have continued to fall. In May, the year-on-year increase in food prices fell to 10.6%; in June, affected by factors such as the slowdown in slaughter of live pigs, the reduction in imports, and the rebound in group consumer demand, pork prices rose slightly from the previous month.
The seasonal changes in fresh vegetable prices are obvious, with an average increase of 3.4% in the first half of the year.
Affected by the high comparison base in the same period last year, the price of fresh fruits continued to decline year-on-year, with an average drop of 13.3% in the first half of the year.
The basic lives of the people are effectively guaranteed, and the overall economic and social situation remains stable and orderly.
With the gradual recovery of transportation and logistics, various regions have increased their efforts to ensure supply, and the market supply and demand situation has improved.
Beginning in March, the CPI fell for four consecutive months, and the year-on-year growth rate dropped from 4.3% in March to 2.5% in June. The overall price level returned to stability.
In the second half of the year, my country's prices will continue to remain at a moderate level, and overall inflationary pressure will not be large, but it is still necessary to promote the restoration of production and living order under the premise of normalizing epidemic prevention and control.
Effectively respond to natural disasters such as floods and droughts in the main agricultural production areas such as grains, fruits and vegetables, strengthen market supervision, and resolutely crack down on behaviors that disrupt market order such as hoarding and price hikes.
