In particular, among crimes that hinder the prevention and control of the epidemic, fraud crimes occur frequently, and the number of people prosecuted by the prosecutors for fraud accounted for 43.4% of all crimes that hinder the prevention and control of the epidemic.
The Supreme People's Procuratorate has carried out targeted guidance. Among the ten batches of typical cases involving epidemic prevention and control that have been released, there are 9 cases involving fraud.
Judging from the case handling by the procuratorial organs in the first half of the year, there are many names involved in fraud crimes, ranging from national macro policies to people’s clothing, food, housing and transportation, including epidemic-related fraud, “medical care” fraud, “health care product” fraud, “admission agency” fraud, The “routine loan” fraud, the fraud of obtaining state subsidies, the fraud of national assets unfreezing, etc., continue to “innovate”, covering education, medical care, employment, pension, social security, land acquisition and demolition, targeted poverty alleviation, financial credit and other fields. The victims caused economic losses and also seriously affected the economic and social development.
In particular, some telecommunications network fraud breaks through the restrictions of national boundaries, regions and personnel, and has the characteristics of stakeholder, cross-border, remote, electronic payment, etc., and there are many unspecified victims and great harm.
For example, some set up specialized companies, rent high-end office buildings, set up multiple departments or positions, use legal network platforms to promote and recruit, train and evaluate recruiters, adopt corporate operation mode management, and wear a “legal cloak” to confuse Stronger sex.
Punishing and preventing crimes in accordance with the law, and promptly issuing early warnings to the public and relevant departments are the unshirkable responsibilities of procuratorial organs.
In judicial case handling, the procuratorial organs earnestly perform their duties, not only insisting on maintaining a high-pressure posture against fraud crimes, but also targeting specific law enforcement measures, and promoting social governance through the formulation and issuance of procuratorial recommendations.
The procuratorial organs strictly control the facts, evidence, procedures, and application of law in approving and prosecuting fraud cases, taking facts as the basis and the law as the criterion, so as to be invincible.
Especially for telecommunication network fraud crimes, we pay attention to the core role of electronic data in fact determination, and strive to build an evidence chain that mutually confirms electronic data, verbal evidence, and documentary evidence.
For example, the Yinzhou District Procuratorate of Ningbo City, Zhejiang Province handled an epidemic-related fraud case, and the prosecutors intervened as soon as possible. From the occurrence of the case to the completion of the case, it only took 5 days, which reflected that it was handled quickly and strictly, and the overall social stability Attitude and determination.
In the process of reviewing arrests and reviewing prosecutions, we focused on the prosecution of missed offenders, corrected the missed arrest of 733 people by public security organs, and corrected the missed review and prosecution of 1,113 co-criminals by public security organs.
In the first half of the year, procuratorial organs across the country issued 298 procuratorial recommendations for fraud crimes, promoting joint efforts to prevent fraud crimes and promoting in-depth governance.
For example, in response to the loopholes in the supervision of telecommunications companies, banks, and intermediary organizations found in the handling of the case, the Guangzhou Procuratorate of Guangdong Province and the Dongguan Procuratorate promptly put forward procuratorial suggestions, urging relevant units to strengthen supervision, improve mechanisms, and promote the leaders. Effective system construction.
The fourth is to make every effort to recover stolen goods and restore damages.
Local procuratorial organs seize important links such as intervening in investigations to guide evidence collection, review and prosecution, supervise investigative agencies to actively recover stolen money, cooperate with relevant departments to recover stolen money, and strive to minimize the economic losses caused by fraud crimes to the people.
For example, the Lin Moumou Routine Loan case handled by the Beijing Municipal Procuratorate involved 22 houses waiting to be sealed up. In the case that the real estate may be dealt with in advance by other cases, the original "Letter of Suspension of Execution" was created and sent to the relevant courts in a timely manner. It is recommended that the court previously closed down the real estate involved in the case to suspend the execution, and after the facts of the crime are ascertained, it will be dealt with in a unified manner, so as to make the greatest efforts to recover the real estate involved in the case and recover the losses of the victims.
The prosecutor reminded everyone to be very vigilant against fraud and crimes. Don't expect "pie in the sky", and don't be credulous when you think it's cheap, and keep your "money bag" safe.
