In the sweltering heat, a reporter from Economic Daily-China Economic Net walked into Zhonghai Village, Yina Town, Weining County, Guizhou Province.
Under the scorching sun, villager Li Yuanzhong was weeding in the base. Although his face was flushed with sun, he hummed a few small songs from time to time.
Weining County, where Yina Town is located, has low latitude, high altitude, sufficient sunlight, and large temperature difference between day and night. The apples produced have high sugar content and good taste. Failed to sell at a good price, failed to form an industry scale.
Yina Town used to be a poor township that "wrapped the valleys and potatoes to survive the spring and autumn". The local poverty incidence was as high as 25.8% 10 years ago.
As the fight against poverty has entered a critical period of decisive victory, it is urgent to change the traditional planting habits, adjust the industrial structure, and increase the income of farmers.
