Membrane separation technology helps crack the "greenhouse effect"-Chinanews
Membrane separation technology helps crack the "greenhouse effect"
Schematic diagram of new mixed matrix membrane preparation technology
Our reporter Shang Rui reported: Recently, the Tianjin University Atmospheric Environment and Bioenergy Team has made significant progress on the "membrane separation method to capture carbon dioxide" and successfully developed a new hybrid matrix membrane preparation technology, which greatly improves the carbon dioxide capture performance of membrane materials.
Related results have been published as the cover article of the international journal "Greenhouse Gas: Science and Technology".
The "greenhouse effect" is a major environmental issue that plagues human development, and carbon dioxide emissions are the culprit responsible for the "greenhouse effect".
How to efficiently capture and use carbon dioxide emitted by humans is the focus of attention of scientists.
"Membrane separation method" is an emerging carbon dioxide capture technology. It separates carbon dioxide gas with the help of membrane materials. It has the characteristics of high efficiency, energy saving and simple operation.
How to let the membrane material "breathe deeply" and improve the efficiency of gas separation is the bottleneck difficulty in the use of membrane separation to capture carbon dioxide.
The scientific research team of Tianjin University has innovated ideas and through repeated experiments, explored the influence of different solvents on the membrane gas separation performance.
The experimental results show that using N-methylpyrrolidone as the preparation solvent, the carbon nanotubes in the produced membrane material are more uniformly distributed and "more air-permeable", which effectively improves the gas separation efficiency and rate of the membrane material.
The mixed matrix membrane prepared by this new technology has a carbon dioxide separation performance close to the current theoretical separation upper limit of this type of membrane material.
"The new technology provides new ideas for the capture of carbon dioxide by membrane separation."
Li Run, a member of Tianjin University's Atmospheric Environment and Bioenergy Team, said: "We hope that this technology can provide strong support for future coal-fired power plants and chemical companies to deal with flue gas, and play a major role in the control of greenhouse gas emissions.
Understand what is a professional grade difference before volunteering to fill in the report-Chinanews.com
2020-07-27 02:22:36 Source: Chongqing Morning News Author: Yu Xiao Editor: Yu Xiao
Understand what is a professional level difference before volunteering
Every year when applying for the college entrance examination, there are students or parents who do not understand the terms involved in the voluntary reporting, which affects the voluntary reporting.
This year, Beijing Jiaotong University, Beijing University of Science and Technology, Beijing University of Posts and Telecommunications, Beijing Forestry University, and Beijing University of Chemical Technology jointly issued the 2020 enrollment policy to cancel the major difference.
What is the meaning of professional grade difference, and what is its significance in voluntary reporting?
There are three ways of professional assignment rules
Experts remind that before filling in the application, you must read the "Admissions Regulations" of your favorite school to understand the admission rules of the college, including the transfer ratio, professional distribution rules, etc.
The rules of major distribution refer to the three main methods of major admission, major priority, score priority, and major difference after colleges are transferred.
The specific method used by colleges and universities will be specified in the "Admissions Regulations".
However, the admission principle of some colleges and universities is to give priority to the total score, and there is no difference between majors.
That is to say, candidates in the admission range are queued according to the total score. When the score does not reach the first professional volunteer admission score, it will be determined whether they have reached the second professional volunteer admission score, and so on until the admission to the last professional volunteer, each professional volunteer There is no level difference between them.
The so-called "professional level difference" refers to the "professional level difference" that the colleges and universities determine the admission majors of volunteer candidates of different majors according to one or several points announced in the admissions regulations when arranging candidates' majors. This point value is the "professional level difference".
That is, the difference between the scores of the colleges and universities in the admission of candidates for the first professional volunteer and the non-first professional volunteer, and the number of grade differences between the professional volunteers, such as 3 points, 2 points, 1 point, etc.
for example.
Suppose that student Xiao Ming applied for college A and scored 560 points. His professional volunteers are: computer, international trade, automation, mechanical engineering, and e-commerce. The professional admission of college A adopts the professional grade difference method, and the grade difference is 2 points and 1 point. , 1 point, 0 point.
When assigning a major, if Xiao Ming’s first major volunteer meets the professional admission requirements and the major has a planned balance, then Xiao Ming is admitted to the "computer" major; if the computer is not admitted, his score will be deducted by 2 points , According to the score of 558 points and the first professional volunteers to apply for "international trade" candidates to determine whether they meet the professional admission requirements; if it still cannot be met, the score is subtracted by 1 point (ie 557 points) for the third professional volunteer "automation" If it is still not satisfied, the score will be subtracted by 1 point (that is, 556 points) for admission to the fourth major. If the follow-up major still cannot meet the professional wishes, the points will no longer be reduced, and so on.
Different universities have different professional level differences
With the popularization of parallel volunteering, many colleges and universities have now cancelled the professional level difference, but some colleges and universities still retain this method this year. According to the "Admissions Regulations" announced by each school, there are mainly more than 20 colleges this year. The professional level is poor.
For example, Sichuan Agricultural University, Shandong University of Science and Technology, Heilongjiang University of Traditional Chinese Medicine, Jiangsu University of Science and Technology, Jiangxi Normal University, Chengdu Medical University, Northeast Dianli University, Jimei University, Nanjing Medical University, Nanjing University of Technology, Ningxia University, Shandong University of Technology, China Civil Aviation Flight Academy, etc.
In these universities, the professional level difference set by each university is different.
Some colleges and universities have a grade difference in each major, such as Ningxia University. Candidates who have already submitted their files to the school will be admitted according to the order in which the candidates fill in the majors.
And some universities have set up different professional level differences between different majors.
For example, Jimei University has a total score of 4 points for the professional volunteer grade, that is, the first professional volunteer and the other professional volunteers have a grade difference of 3 points. There is no level difference between other professional volunteers, which is regarded as parallel volunteers, and other professional volunteers and transfer professional volunteers are majors The level difference is 1 point.
When filling in their volunteers, candidates and parents must carefully read the admission policy of the school reported to see if there is a professional grade difference and what the form of the grade difference is. While fully considering the scores, they must also reasonably analyze the school and major to be selected. , If the college adopts the grade difference method for admission in the admissions charter, candidates should pay attention to the gradient between the majors when choosing a major to increase the chance of admission.
